---
title: Hot Honey Chicken with BBQ-Roasted Potatoes & Buttery Broccoli
description: Crispy panko-coated chicken, smoky barbecue-spiced potatoes, and easy-peasy steamed broccoli are a pretty obvious recipe for dinnertime success. It’s got your classic trifecta of meat, potatoes, and veg—could you ask for much more? How about a drizzle of hot honey? The stuff combines sweet sensations with spicy good vibrations, making it perfect for taking things beyond ordinary.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5f999485d31ec3541e04fe18-03301cd0.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/hot-honey-chicken-5f999485d31ec3541e04fe18-25aa7d9d.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/hot-honey-chicken-5f999485d31ec3541e04fe18
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 58 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 390 mg
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
---

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{a drizzle}, half the @Sweet and Smoky BBQ Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @pepper{a big pinch}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Set aside.

Place @Butter{2%tablespoons}(for 2 servings) in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in a large drizzle of olive oil, remaining BBQ Seasoning, pepper, and a big pinch of salt. Add @Panko Breadcrumbs{½%cup} and stir until evenly combined.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper.

Lightly oil a second baking sheet; spread chicken out across sheet. Evenly spread @Sour Cream{2%tablespoons} onto tops of chicken; mound with panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Roast potatoes on top rack until crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Once potatoes have roasted 5 minutes, add chicken to middle rack and roast until browned and cooked through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cut @Broccoli Florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Place in a large microwave-safe bowl with @water{1%teaspoon}. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{} and poke a few holes in wrap. Microwave until broccoli is tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Carefully remove plastic wrap (watch out for steam). Drain any water left in bowl, then toss broccoli with @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide chicken, potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Drizzle chicken with as much @Mike's Hot Honey®{¾%ounce} as you like and serve.

> This recipe combines crispy panko-coated chicken, smoky barbecue-spiced potatoes, and easy steamed broccoli with a drizzle of hot honey for dinnertime success.